<br>
I usually pay 5p for HQ brute hides (needed for the reinforced), and have traded a pair of boots for ten HQ hides.<br>
<br>
Thimble Leatherpad<br>
Druid 35<br>
Mith Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukbern.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kbern</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/26/01 6:22:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vale Armor</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the information all.  I found a tailor on Drinal and was referred to him by some friends of mine and guildies of his.<br>
<br>
This was guy was awesome and set me up with boots, pants, belt and cloak for free..FREE!!<br>
<br>
I just gave him all the reg brute hides i had, a plains pebble, and promised him any brute hides I get will go to him..the last part was my addition since it is the least I can do for him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulyberniabelisama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lybernia Belisama</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.sherilyn.net/pendulum/icon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/26/01 9:42:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/sherilyn70/lybernia4a.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vale Armor</span><hr size=1> Thank you very much for those boots Thimble.  :)  I knew it was somewhere around 400 but didn't remember the exact price you were asking for them.  Didn't know you hung out here as well.   <p><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/sherilyn70/lybernia.GIF><BR>
